LABEL: chapter house
DEFINITION: A building or room that is part of a cathedral, monastery or collegiate church, in which larger meetings are held.

LABEL: Kaaba
DEFINITION: A building at the center of Islam's most important mosque, Great Mosque of Mecca.

LABEL: mosque
DEFINITION: A place of worship for Muslims.

LABEL: listed building
DEFINITION: A building that has been placed on one of the four statutory lists maintained by Historic England in England, Historic Environment Scotland in Scotland, Cadw in Wales, and the Northern Ireland Environment Agency in Northern Ireland.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: The term has also been used in Ireland, where buildings are surveyed for the National Inventory of Architectural Heritage in accordance with the country's obligations under the Granada Convention. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Listed_building)

LABEL: bunkhouse
DEFINITION: A barracks-like building.
Example of use: Historically bunkhouses were used to house working cowboys on ranches in North America.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Historically used to house working cowboys on ranches in North America. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bunkhouse)

LABEL: corn exchange
DEFINITION: A building where merchants trade grains.

LABEL: oast house
DEFINITION: A building designed for kilning (drying) hops.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: As part of the hops brewing process. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oast_house)

LABEL: orangery
DEFINITION: A room or building that formed a very large fruit tree green house, or conservatory, on the grounds of fashionable residences from the 17th to the 19th centuries.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Where orange and other fruit trees were protected during the winter. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orangery)

LABEL: skyscraper
DEFINITION: A continuously habitable high-rise building that has over 40 floors and is taller than 150 m (492 ft).

LABEL: tenement
DEFINITION: A type of building shared by multiple dwellings, typically with flats or apartments on each floor and with shared entrance stairway access.

LABEL: mausoleum
DEFINITION: An external, free-standing building constructed as a monument enclosing the interment space or burial chamber of a deceased person or people.

LABEL: bowling alley
DEFINITION: A sports facility where bowling is played.

LABEL: hangar
DEFINITION: A closed building structure to hold aircraft or spacecraft.

LABEL: bistro
DEFINITION: A small restaurant.
OLD DEFINITION: A bistro is a small restaurant, serving moderately priced simple meals in a modest setting with alcohol. Bistros are defined mostly by the foods they serve.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Bistros serve moderately priced, simple meal in a modest setting with alcohol, and are defined mostly by the foods they serve. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bistro)

LABEL: brasserie
DEFINITION: A type of French restaurant which provides more service or food variety than a bistro.
OLD DEFINITION: A brasserie is a type of French restaurant with a relaxed setting, which serves single dishes and other meals.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment:  Has a relaxed setting and serves single dishes and other meals.The word brasserie is also French for "brewery" and, by extension, "the brewing business". (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brasserie)

LABEL: cafeteria
DEFINITION: A food service location in which there is little or no waiting staff table service.
OLD DEFINITION: A cafeteria is a type of food service location in which there is little or no waiting staff table service, whether a restaurant or within an institution such as a large office building or school.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: May occur in a restaurant or within an institution such as a large office building or school. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cafeteria)

LABEL: carvery
DEFINITION: A pub or restaurant where cooked meat is freshly sliced to order for customers.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Sometimes offering unlimited servings in a buffet style for a fixed price. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carvery)

LABEL: coffeehouse
DEFINITION: An establishment that primarily serves coffee.
Example of use: A coffeehouse often offers italian style  espresso, latte, and cappuccino drinks.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Serves espresso, latte, cappuccino, etc. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coffeehouse)

LABEL: greasy spoon
DEFINITION: A small, cheap eatery typically specializing in fried foods and/or home-cooked meals.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: An American diner or coffee shop, or a British or Irish cafe. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greasy_spoon)

LABEL: steakhouse
DEFINITION: A restaurant that specializes in steaks and chops.

LABEL: trattoria
DEFINITION: An Italian-style eating establishment that is generally less formal than a ristorante, but more formal than an osteria.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: A trattoria rooted in tradition may typically provide no printed menu, casual service, wine sold by the decanter rather than the bottle, and low prices, with an emphasis on a steady clientele rather than on haute cuisine. Food tends to be modest but plentiful (mostly following regional and local recipes), sometimes even served family-style, at common tables. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trattoria)

LABEL: cottage hospital
DEFINITION: A semi-obsolete type of small hospital.
Example of use: A cottage hospital is commonly found in the United Kingdom.
ISSUES / COMMENTS:
healthcare facility ( a new term)

Comment: Most commonly found in the United Kingdom. The original concept was a small rural building having several beds that had the ability to provide rurual communities with the facilities to deal immediately with emergencies. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cottage_hospital)

LABEL: field hospital
DEFINITION: A temporary hospital or mobile medical unit that takes care of casualties on-site before they can be safely transported to more permanent facilities.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: healthcare facility ( a new term)

LABEL: hospice
DEFINITION: A healthcare facility that focuses on palliative care for the terminally ill.
ISSUES / COMMENTS:
healthcare facility ( a new term)

Comment: Focuses on the palliation of a terminally ill patient's pain and symptoms and attending to their emotional and spiritual needs at the end of life. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hospice)

LABEL: movie theater
DEFINITION: A building that contains auditoria for viewing films.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Primarily used for entertainment purposes. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Movie_theater)

LABEL: warehouse
DEFINITION: A building for storing goods.

LABEL: town hall
DEFINITION: A town hall is the chief administrative building of a city, town, or other municipality.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Usually houses the city or town council, its associated departments, and their employees. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Town_hall)

LABEL: leisure centre
DEFINITION: A building or site where people go to keep fit or relax through using the facilities.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Usually owned and operated by the city, borough council or municipal district council. Facilities may include a swimming pool (many with water slide), large sports hall, squash courts, cafeteria, licensed bar, fitness suite, aerobics studios, outdoor grass and/or artificial pitches for football (soccer), hockey etc., a solarium, sauna and/or steam room.(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leisure_centre)

LABEL: business park
DEFINITION: An area of land on which office buildings are grouped.

LABEL: game reserve
DEFINITION: An area of land where wild animals live safely or are hunted in a controlled way for sport.

LABEL: hillock
DEFINITION: A small hill, usually separated from a larger group of hills such as a range.
Comment: Hillocks are similar in their distribution and size to small mesas or buttes.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Hillocks are similar in their distribution and size to small mesas or buttes. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hillock)

LABEL: riverfront
DEFINITION: A shoreline region along a river.

LABEL: skerry
DEFINITION: A small rocky island, or islet, usually too small for human habitation.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Usually too small for human habitation. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skerry)

LABEL: wind farm
DEFINITION: A group of wind turbines in the same location used to produce electricity.
Exact Synonym@en: wind park|wind power station|wind power plant

LABEL: desert island
DEFINITION: An island, islet or atoll that is not permanently populated by humans.

LABEL: big-box store
DEFINITION: A physically large retail establishment.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Usually part of a chain of stores. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Big-box_store)

LABEL: Bailey bridge
DEFINITION: A type of portable, pre-fabricated, truss bridge.

LABEL: drawbridge
DEFINITION: A hinged bridge which can be raised.
Example of use: A drawbridge is often at the entrance to a castle or tower surrounded by a moat, and is also found on rail lines that cross shipping water lanes.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Typically at the entrance to a castle or tower surrounded by a moat. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drawbridge)

LABEL: footbridge
DEFINITION: A bridge designed solely for pedestrians.

LABEL: humpback bridge
DEFINITION: An arch bridge, where the span is higher than the ramps on either side, forming a hump-like arrangement.

LABEL: overpass
DEFINITION: A bridge, road, railway or similar structure that crosses over another road or railway.

LABEL: suspension bridge
DEFINITION: A bridge in which the deck is hung on vertical suspenders via suspension cables.

LABEL: swing bridge
DEFINITION: A movable bridge that has as a vertical locating pin, as its primary structural support, and a support ring about which the turning can can pivot horizontally.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: The vertical locating pin and support ring are usually located at or near to its center of gravity. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swing_bridge)

LABEL: vacuum cleaner
DEFINITION: A device that causes suction in order to remove debris from surfaces.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Removes debris from floors, upholstery, draperies and other surfaces.	(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vacuum_cleaner)

LABEL: chicken manure
DEFINITION: An animal manure made of chicken feces.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Used as an organic fertilizer, especially for soil low in nitrogen. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chicken_manure)

LABEL: gypsum
DEFINITION: A soft sulfate mineral composed of calcium sulfate dihydrate.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Chemical formula CaSO4·2H2O. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gypsum)

LABEL: water tank
DEFINITION: A container for storing water.

LABEL: water trough
DEFINITION: A receptacle intended to provide drinking water to animals.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Human-made or natural receptacle. Generally intended to provide drinking water to animals, livestock on farms, livesotck on ranches, or wild animals. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Watering_trough)

LABEL: wet wipe
DEFINITION: A small moistened piece of plastic or cloth.
Example of use: A wet wipe often comes folded and individually wrapped for convenience.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Often comes folded and individually wrapped for convenience. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wet_wipe)

LABEL: barn
DEFINITION: An agricultural building.
OLD DEFINITION: A barn is an agricultural building usually on farms and used for various purposes.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Usually on farms and used for various purposes. In the North American area, a barn refers to structures that house livestock, including cattle and horses, as well as equipment and fodder, and often grain. In the British Isles, the term barn is restricted mainly to storage structures for unthreshed cereals and fodder. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barn)

LABEL: chicken house
DEFINITION: A small house where fowl are kept.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Typically where female chickens or other fowl are kept safe and secure. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chicken_coop)

LABEL: litter
DEFINITION: Waste products that have been discarded at an unsuitable location.
ISSUES / COMMENTS:
animal litter could actually go under it once introduced. 

Comment: Discarded incorrectly, without consent. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Litter)

LABEL: sewing table
DEFINITION: A table or desk used for sewing.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Litter consists of waste products that have been discarded incorrectly, without consent, at an unsuitable location.

LABEL: wheel
DEFINITION: A disk-shaped material that rotates around an axle bearing placed through a hole in its center.

LABEL: tray
DEFINITION: A shallow platform designed for the carrying of items.

LABEL: tool
DEFINITION: An object used to extend the ability of an individual to modify features of the surrounding environment.

LABEL: squeegee
DEFINITION: A tool with a flat, smooth rubber blade, used to remove or control the flow of liquid on a flat surface.
Example of use: A squeegee is used for cleaning and in printing.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: It is used for cleaning and in printing. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Squeegee)

LABEL: public toilet
DEFINITION: A room or small building with toilets (or urinals) and sinks that does not belong to a particular household.

LABEL: pump
DEFINITION: A pump is a device that moves fluids (liquids or gases), or sometimes slurries, by mechanical action.

LABEL: peeler
DEFINITION: A kitchen tool, used to remove the outer layer of vegetables and fruit, consisting of a handle attached to a metal blade with a slot with a sharp edge.
Example of use: A peeler can be used to remove the outer layer (the "skin" or "peel") of some vegetables such as potatoes, broccoli stalks, and carrots, and fruits such as apples and pears.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Used to remove the outer layer (the "skin" or "peel") of some vegetables such as potatoes, broccoli stalks, and carrots, and fruits such as apples and pears. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peeler)

LABEL: pallet
DEFINITION: A flat transport structure which supports goods in a stable fashion while being lifted and/or moved.
Example of use: A pallet can be moved using a forklift, a pallet jack, a front loader, a jacking device, or an erect crane.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Designed to be lifted by a forklift, a pallet jack, a front loader, a jacking device, or an erect crane. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pallet)

LABEL: packing machine
DEFINITION: Machinery used throughout all packaging operations.
ISSUES / COMMENTS: Comment: Involving primary packages to distribution packs. Includes many packaging processes: fabrication, cleaning, filling, sealing, combining, labeling, overwrapping, palletizing. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Packaging_machinery)
